		<p>Quiz game developed in R using Shiny, to help identify various Orthoptera species by matching the species name to sound and image cues.
Recordings and pictures are specific to Eastern Texas and recordings were collected from <a href="https://orthsoc.org/sina/index.htm" target="_blank">Orthopterists' Society</a> (T.J. Walker, T.M.Yawn)<br><br>
This project is to help educate researchers and the general public, on common cricket species, and is part of a broader initiative to record cricket calls and classify orthoptera calls using raven pro.<br>
Contributed to dataset creation and collaborated on development of the Shiny interface.<br>This is an ongoing project and that I will continue to work on with PhD Student Joe Elias over the summer<br><br><i>Website coming soon!</i><br>- Reasurch in Dr. Eliza Grames Lab</p>
